<h2 id="comparison-group-a">Top 5: Low-Cost Leaders</h2>

Fee efficiency is the single biggest predictor of long-term investment success. A 0.50% annual fee difference compounds into **$47,000+ over 30 years** on a $100,000 portfolio (assuming 7% annual returns). But headline fees can be misleading — you must account for underlying ETF expense ratios, cash allocations, and any hidden costs that reduce your effective equity exposure. The platforms below offer the lowest total cost of ownership in the robo-advisor market, each with a different approach to minimizing the drag on your compounding.

