<h2 id="comparison-group-b">Top 5: Feature Specialists</h2>

While cost matters, sophisticated investors often need capabilities that go beyond low fees. Tax-loss harvesting alone can add **1.0–1.8% in annual after-tax alpha** — far exceeding the 0.25% fee most platforms charge. Direct indexing amplifies this further for portfolios above $100,000 by enabling per-security loss harvesting that ETF-level TLH cannot capture. The platforms below lead in advanced capabilities: Betterment's Black-Litterman portfolio construction methodology, Wealthfront's daily TLH monitoring with Gordon Growth Model-derived equity allocations, and specialized tools like 529 college savings plans and micro-investing roundups that competitors simply don't offer.

