### Robinhood Strategies

Robinhood Strategies launched in early 2025 as the trading platform's entry into automated portfolio management, introducing a pricing model no competitor has matched: a hard cap of $250 per year on advisory fees for Gold members. At the standard 0.25% rate, any portfolio above $100,000 effectively pays less than 0.25%, with a $500,000 portfolio paying just 0.05% in management costs. For large-balance investors, this makes Robinhood Strategies the cheapest managed option available — undercutting even Schwab's zero-fee model when accounting for Schwab's cash drag on equivalent portfolio sizes.

The platform's other distinction is portfolio construction that includes individual stocks alongside ETFs, giving investors exposure to specific companies within their automated allocation — a feature unique among robo-advisors. Robinhood Gold membership ($5/month) is required, but Gold also includes 4.00% APY on uninvested cash, NASDAQ Level II data, and professional research reports. Our testing confirmed smooth portfolio transitions from existing Robinhood holdings and responsive automatic rebalancing. The absence of tax-loss harvesting and restricted account types (individual taxable and IRA only) are the primary limitations for investors who need advanced tax optimization or complex account structures.

