Regardless of which platform you choose, the single most important step is starting. Every year of delay costs compounding time that cannot be recovered. A $10,000 initial investment at age 25 grows to approximately **$150,000** by age 65 at 7% annual returns — but waiting until 35 reduces that to roughly $76,000. Every robo-advisor listed above can be opened in under 10 minutes, funded via ACH transfer, and configured with automatic monthly deposits. The mathematics of compounding are unforgiving toward procrastination and indifferent to which specific platform you select — what matters is that you begin.

