<h2 id="methodology">Our Methodology</h2>

Our evaluation framework applies the four quality criteria identified in this analysis — conflict of interest, asset class selection, expense ratios, and systematic risk measurement — alongside practical usability testing. Each platform was scored across 240+ individual data points weighted to reflect the factors that most directly impact long-term investor outcomes:

<MethodologyBox
  title="How We Evaluate Robo-Advisors"
  steps={[
    "Fee structure & conflict analysis — management fees, ETF expense ratios, cash drag, and revenue model alignment (25% weight)",
    "Tax optimization assessment — TLH frequency (daily vs. periodic), direct indexing availability, and tax-alpha modeling (20% weight)",
    "Portfolio construction methodology — MVO variant used, capital market assumptions transparency, asset class rationale (15% weight)",
    "Account type coverage — IRA variants, Trust, 401(k), 529, custodial, and tax-coordinated placement (10% weight)",
    "Investment selection — ETF quality, diversification breadth, weighted-average expense ratios (10% weight)",
    "Risk measurement — standard deviation, max drawdown, Sharpe ratio disclosure, stress testing documentation (5% weight)",
    "Platform usability — UX testing across web and mobile, onboarding speed, behavioral guardrails (5% weight)",
    "Human advisor access — CFP availability, response times, quality of advice (5% weight)",
    "Regulatory positioning — FINRA 2026 readiness, cybersecurity posture, GenAI governance (5% weight)"
  ]}
  dataPoints={240}
  hoursResearch={80}
/>

